- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `arr` must contain unique integers from 1 to the length of the array.
- The length of the integer array parameter `arr` is less than or equal to 100.
- The integer array result must contain valid `k` values corresponding to a sequence of pancake flips that sort the array `arr`.
- The integer array result must be empty if the input array `arr` is already sorted.
- The number of pancake flips performed must be within 10 times the length of the array `arr`.